<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
Macrocarpus (Greek) 'makros', large; and 'karpos', fruit (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-662-07125-0" author="Eggli, U" journalOrPublisher="Springer Science &amp; Business Media, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" refId="B19" refString="Eggli, U, Newton, LE, 2004. Etymological Dictionary of Succulent Plant Names. Springer Science &amp; Business Media, Berlin, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-662-07125-0" title="Etymological Dictionary of Succulent Plant Names." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-662-07125-0" year="2004">Eggli and Newton 2004</bibRefCitation>
